      "sections": {
        "Summary": "From unity arises polarity—the dance of perceiver and perceived, the birth of relationship.",
        "Interpretation": "### The Dance of Existence  \nThis card illustrates the continuous interplay between the self and the other, emphasizing the relational aspect of being.  \nTillich discusses the importance of relationships in understanding existence. By framing this duality as a \"dance,\" the card highlights the dynamic interactions that shape our experiences and perceptions, reminding us that we are never isolated but always in connection with the world around us."
